# Nepali Unicode Plugin for WinterCMS

[![License: MIT](https://img.shields.io/badge/License-MIT-yellow.svg)](https://opensource.org/licenses/MIT)

Nepali Unicode plugin for WinterCMS converts Nepali fonts like **Preeti** and **Hisab** into standard **Nepali Unicode**. 
---

## Features

- Convert Preeti/Hisab text to Nepali Unicode automatically.
- Easy to install and use.
- Open-source and MIT licensed.

---

## Installation

### Using Composer (Recommended)

1. Navigate to your WinterCMS project folder:

```bash
cd /path/to/your/wintercms
````

2. Install the plugin via Composer:

```bash
composer require spanjaan/wn-nepaliunicode-plugin
```
---

### Manual Installation

1. Download the repository from GitHub:

```bash
git clone https://github.com/spanjaan/wn-nepaliunicode-plugin.git
```

2. Move the plugin folder to:

```
/plugins/spanjaan/nepaliunicode
```

---

## Usage

### Adding the Unicode Converter to a CMS Page

1. Open your CMS page in the Winter CMS backend
2. Add the following component to your page:
```ini
[unicodeConverter]
```
3. Save the page

The Unicode Converter component will now be available on your page. You can place it anywhere in your page content using:
```twig
{% component 'unicodeConverter' %}
```

